INSERT INTO `minutes` (`id`, `subject`, `time`, `meeting_id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1, 'dasdsa asdaa', '11:00:00', 2, '2023-07-05 20:59:17', '2023-07-05 21:14:59'),
(13, 'Each attendee introduced themselves.', '09:30:00', 58, '2023-07-09 19:18:04', '2023-07-09 19:18:04'),
(14, 'Discussion on the Importance of Supporting Orphans :\nMr. Maged Amin Discussed how is supporting orphans is a topic of great significance, contributing not just to the welfare of individual children but also to broader societal development.', '09:55:00', 58, '2023-07-09 19:20:41', '2023-07-09 19:20:41'),
(15, 'Introduction and discussion of idea for Orphans\' Celebration Day :\nMr. Maged Amin presented an overview of Organize a special event such as a fun fair or carnival. Include games, face painting, magic shows, and other child-friendly activities. \nAlso Host a talent show where the children can showcase their talents like singing, dancing, painting, etc. This can help boost their confidence. \nAnd Gift Giving: Arrange for each child to receive a gift. It doesn\'t have to be expensive; a small toy, a book, or even clothes can make a child feel special.', '10:40:00', 58, '2023-07-09 19:24:33', '2023-07-09 19:24:33'),
(16, 'Discussion on Venue Preparation and Setup:\nMr. Maged Amin presented an overview of Planning and setting up a venue for an Orphans\' Celebration Day can be a fun and rewarding task. Here are some ideas to consider:\n1. Theme Selection: Select a fun, child-friendly theme for the day. Themes could range from popular children\'s movies or books, to broader themes like superheroes, animals, or a color-themed party.\n2. Decoration: Decorate the venue according to the chosen theme. Use balloons, streamers, banners, and themed tablecloths. You could create a special backdrop for photos.\n3. Activity Stations: Set up different activity stations around the venue. This could include a games area, arts and crafts station, face painting corner, or a storytelling spot.', '10:50:00', 58, '2023-07-09 19:25:55', '2023-07-09 19:25:55'),
(17, 'Discussion on Potential dates for the event :\nThe members of the board of directors discussed setting a suitable date for the ceremony, and the initial agreement was that the celebration would take place during the month of April', '10:55:00', 58, '2023-07-09 19:27:33', '2023-07-09 19:27:33'),
(18, 'Action Items and Next Steps :\nChristina will schedule another meeting Mar 21.2019', '11:30:00', 58, '2023-07-09 19:40:32', '2023-07-10 09:04:19'),
(19, 'Introduction and Welcome :\nWelcome to this important meeting dedicated to planning for the upcoming Orphans\' Celebration Day. We are gathered here today with a shared purpose - to create a memorable and joyous event for the orphans in our community.', '09:30:00', 59, '2023-07-10 10:10:45', '2023-07-10 10:10:45'),
(20, 'Review of the previous meeting :\nMr. Majed Amin reviewed what was discussed at the previous meeting about the idea and the Importance of Orphans\' Celebration Day', '09:35:00', 59, '2023-07-10 10:16:33', '2023-07-10 10:16:33'),
(21, 'Discussion on Budgeting for the event :\nMr. Majed Amin discussed Budgeting for Orphans\' Celebration Day, Budgeting is a crucial part of planning for the Orphans\' Celebration Day. It ensures that we have allocated resources appropriately and can meet all the needs of the event without financial strain. Here are some key points to consider:\n\n\n1. Venue Costs: If the venue isn\'t donated or available for free, there will be costs associated with renting the space. We need to factor this into our budget.\n\n\n2. Food and Beverages: We need to estimate the cost of providing meals and drinks for the children and volunteers. This could include snacks, a main meal, and possibly a celebratory cake or dessert.\n\n\n3. Decorations: The budget should include an allocation for decorations. This will depend on the theme and scale of the event.\n\n4. Activities: The cost of activities will vary depending on what we decide to include. This could range from hiring entertainers, equipment rental for games, art supplies for craft activities, etc.', '10:08:00', 59, '2023-07-10 10:28:18', '2023-07-10 10:28:18'),
(22, 'Discussion on Activities and Programs for the event :\nThe members of the board of directors discussed the proposed activities and they agreed about Planning engaging and entertaining activities and programs . These activities should be age-appropriate, inclusive, and fun. Here are some points to consider:\n\n\n1. Interactive Games: Games are a great way to keep children engaged and entertained. We could include traditional games like sack races or musical chairs, or try something new like a treasure hunt or an obstacle course.\n\n\n2. Talent Show: A talent show can provide an opportunity for the children to showcase their skills and talents. This can boost their self-confidence and also serves as a form of entertainment for everyone.\n\n\n3. Art and Craft Sessions: Organizing art and craft sessions can encourage creativity among children. This could involve painting, making DIY crafts, or even a group mural that can be displayed after the event.', '10:18:00', 59, '2023-07-10 10:55:21', '2023-07-10 10:55:21'),
(23, 'Discussion on Volunteer recruitment and roles :\nBoard members discussed how volunteers play a crucial role in making the Orphans\' Celebration Day a success. They help ensure the event runs smoothly and provide essential support to the children and organizers.', '10:40:00', 59, '2023-07-10 11:06:23', '2023-07-10 11:06:23'),
(24, 'Action Items and Next Steps :\nAs we conclude this meeting, it\'s crucial to clearly outline the actions each board member needs to take to ensure the success of our Orphans\' Celebration Day. Here are the next steps:\n\n1. Budget Approval: The proposed budget needs to be reviewed and approved by the board. Any necessary adjustments should be made promptly.\n\n2. Venue Confirmation: The selected venue needs to be booked and confirmed. Ensure that all necessary arrangements, such as seating, stage setup, and safety measures, are in place.\n\n3. Meeting Schedule: Schedule the next board meeting to review progress and address any issues.', '11:04:00', 59, '2023-07-10 11:22:14', '2023-07-10 16:44:37'),
(25, 'Introduction and Welcome :\nMr.Maged Amin opened the meeting with a warm welcome and emphasized the importance of planning a memorable event for the orphans', '09:35:00', 60, '2023-07-10 13:27:18', '2023-07-10 13:27:18'),
(26, 'Review of the previous meeting :\nThe minutes from the previous meeting were reviewed and approved with no objections', '09:40:00', 60, '2023-07-10 13:32:33', '2023-07-10 13:32:33'),
(27, 'Discussion about the participation of the regional director of the group in the celebration :\n It was discussed and agreed that the regional director of the group would be invited to participate in the celebration.', '10:15:00', 60, '2023-07-10 13:35:02', '2023-07-10 13:35:02'),
(28, 'Online meeting with the group\'s regional director in Egypt and the Middle East :\nAn online meeting was held with the group\'s regional manager in Egypt and the Middle East, and her participation in the celebration was discussed, and she was very welcomed and discussed some details with the board members .', '10:30:00', 60, '2023-07-10 13:51:30', '2023-07-10 13:51:30'),
(29, 'Discussion on A plan to source and arrange gifts for the orphans :\nMany ideas were put forward for gifts, including donations and the purchase of gifts using the collected funds, which will be transferred to the representative of the group in Qena governorate to buy in-kind gifts for children and festive supplies', '11:15:00', 60, '2023-07-10 13:59:53', '2023-07-10 13:59:53'),
(30, 'Discussion on volunteer recruitment strategies and defining their roles :\nStrategies for recruiting volunteers were discussed, The roles of volunteers were also defined, including game coordinators, food servers, and safety monitors.', '11:30:00', 60, '2023-07-10 14:21:17', '2023-07-10 14:21:17'),
(31, 'Agreement on the date of the celebration :\nAfter some discussion, it was agreed that the celebration will take place on Apr 13, 2019', '11:55:00', 60, '2023-07-10 14:24:57', '2023-07-10 14:24:57'),
(32, 'Action Items and Next Steps :\nEach board member was given specific tasks to complete before the next meeting, including finalizing the budget, confirming the venue, and starting Communication with volunteers', '12:05:00', 60, '2023-07-10 14:29:19', '2023-07-10 14:29:19'),
(33, '-	The transfer of a financial amount to the representative of the group in Qena governorate will be discussed to prepare for the celebration :\n- A discussion was held regarding the transfer of a specific financial amount to the representative of the group in Qena governorate to prepare for the celebration. It was agreed that Mr. Maged Amin would handle the transaction and provide a report on its completion.', '09:30:00', 61, '2023-07-10 16:36:37', '2023-07-10 16:36:37'),
(34, '-	Discussing the filming of the celebration to design videos and publish them on social networking sites and publish them in the media .\n\n- The board discussed the importance of filming the celebration to create videos for social media and press releases. It was agreed that a professional videographer would be hired to capture high-quality footage of the event.', '10:00:00', 61, '2023-07-10 16:38:21', '2023-07-10 16:38:21'),
(35, '-	Discussion of the final program of the celebration:\nThe final program of the celebration was discussed in detail. This included the sequence of activities, guest speakers, entertainment, and timing of each segment.', '10:20:00', 61, '2023-07-10 16:41:25', '2023-07-10 16:41:25'),
(36, 'Introduction and Welcome:\nDr.Mona Tantawi provided a warm welcome to all attendees and shared the purpose of the meeting.', '09:30:00', 62, '2023-07-11 12:40:44', '2023-07-13 11:49:35'),
(37, 'Presentation of the Current Situation at the Kidney Disease Center in Mansoura : \nA detailed presentation was given on the current situation at the Kidney Disease Center in Mansoura, shedding light on the challenges faced by the center and areas where support is needed.', '09:45:00', 62, '2023-07-11 12:49:58', '2023-07-11 12:49:58'),
(38, 'Discussion on Potential Support Ideas :\nSeveral ideas were brought forward on how to best support the center, including fundraising initiatives, media campaigns and more.', '10:20:00', 62, '2023-07-11 12:56:31', '2023-07-12 09:12:37'),
(39, 'Breakout Session for Brainstorming :\nAttendees split into smaller groups to brainstorm additional ways to support the center.\neach member presented an ideas, which were discussed amongst the group. Mr. Majed Amin presented the idea of filming the center and doing an interview with Dr. Mohammed Ghoneim, founder of the Center for kidney diseases, in addition to producing a number of videos to invite donors to support the center', '11:00:00', 62, '2023-07-11 13:01:43', '2023-07-11 13:08:26'),
(40, 'Action Plan and Next Steps:\nAn action plan was created outlining the next steps for each initiative. Responsibilities were assigned to ensure follow-through', '11:30:00', 62, '2023-07-11 13:11:29', '2023-07-11 13:11:29'),
(41, 'Introduction and Welcome:\nDr.Mona Tantawi provided a warm welcome to all attendees and shared the purpose of the meeting.', '09:30:00', 63, '2023-07-11 18:37:52', '2023-07-13 12:39:34'),
(42, '- Overview of the previous meeting\nThe previous meeting and the suggestions and results were reviewed', '09:35:00', 63, '2023-07-11 19:06:40', '2023-07-11 19:06:40'),
(43, '-Overview of the Kidney Disease Center\'s Needs\nA detailed presentation was given on the current state of the Kidney Disease Center and its specific needs which the fundraising event aims to address.', '09:50:00', 63, '2023-07-11 19:08:47', '2023-07-11 19:08:47'),
(44, '-Purpose of the Fundraising Event\nThe group discussed the primary goals of the fundraising event, including the financial target and the intended use of the funds raised.', '10:25:00', 63, '2023-07-11 19:24:03', '2023-07-11 19:24:03'),
(45, '-Presentation and Discussion of Proposed Fundraising Ideas\nEach member presented his ideas, which were discussed among all participants.\nA proposal was made to invite one of the stars to participate in the event . The names of some of the international bodies participating in this event were presented. It was also proposed to invite the consul general to attend the event and give a speech', '10:40:00', 63, '2023-07-11 19:29:23', '2023-07-11 19:29:23'),
(46, '-Development of an Action Plan and Task Assignments\nAn action plan was created, outlining the tasks necessary to execute the fundraising event. Responsibilities were assigned to ensure follow-through.', '11:10:00', 63, '2023-07-11 19:31:18', '2023-07-11 19:31:18'),
(47, 'Closing Remarks and Adjournment:\nThe meeting was concluded by Mrs. Aida Elmanzalawi at 11:15 am, with thanks given to all attendees for their valuable contributions.', '11:00:00', 63, '2023-07-11 20:20:07', '2023-07-11 20:20:07'),
(48, '-Introduction and Welcome\nMr.Maged Amin welcomed all attendees and explained the purpose of the meeting .', '09:30:00', 52, '2023-07-12 09:54:00', '2023-07-12 09:54:00'),
(49, 'Overview of Eid al-Adha Sacrifices Tradition : \nThe group reviewed the tradition of Eid al-Adha sacrifices, emphasizing its significance and the importance of distributing to those in need.', '09:35:00', 52, '2023-07-12 09:55:14', '2023-07-12 09:55:14'),
(50, 'Purpose of the Sacrifices Distribution:\nThe primary goals of the distribution were discussed, including reaching as many needy individuals as possible and ensuring a fair distribution process.', '09:50:00', 52, '2023-07-12 09:56:03', '2023-07-12 09:56:03'),
(51, 'Presentation and Discussion of Proposed Distribution Strategies:\nEach member presented his ideas, which were discussed among all members.', '10:10:00', 52, '2023-07-12 09:59:14', '2023-07-12 09:59:14'),
(52, 'Selection of Final Distribution Plan:\nAfter thorough discussion, the group collectively agreed on the final plan for the sacrifices distribution', '10:30:00', 52, '2023-07-12 10:01:49', '2023-07-12 10:01:49'),
(53, 'Development of an Action Plan and Task Assignments:\nAn action plan was created, outlining the tasks necessary to execute the distribution event. Responsibilities were assigned to ensure follow-through.', '11:29:00', 52, '2023-07-12 10:03:55', '2023-07-12 10:03:55'),
(54, 'Closing Remarks :\nThe meeting was concluded by Mr.Maged Amin at 12:00 pm, with thanks given to all attendees for their valuable contributions.', '12:00:00', 52, '2023-07-12 10:06:20', '2023-07-12 10:06:20'),
(55, 'Introduction and Welcome:\nMr. Majid Amin welcomed all attendees and outlined the purpose of the meeting.', '09:30:00', 53, '2023-07-12 10:58:09', '2023-07-12 10:58:09'),
(56, 'Recap of First Meeting:\nA brief recap of the first meeting was given, reminding everyone of the decisions made and ideas proposed.', '09:40:00', 53, '2023-07-12 10:58:35', '2023-07-12 10:58:35'),
(57, 'Discussion on Practical Steps for Implementation:\nThe team discussed the practical steps needed to implement the process of purchasing, slaughtering, and distribution of the calves.', '09:45:00', 53, '2023-07-12 10:59:16', '2023-07-12 10:59:16'),
(58, 'Presentation of Proposed Purchase, Slaughter, and Distribution Plan:\nThe idea of buying 2 calves and distributing their meat in the governorates of Cairo, Alexandria, Beheira, and Damanhour was presented and discussed.', '09:50:00', 53, '2023-07-12 10:59:48', '2023-07-12 10:59:48'),
(59, 'Scheduling a Zoom Meeting with Mr. Mohammed Al-dawy:\nIt was agreed that a Zoom meeting would be scheduled with Mr. Mohammed Al-dawy, the treasurer of the group\'s branch in Cairo, to discuss the details of the purchase, slaughter, and distribution process.', '10:00:00', 53, '2023-07-12 11:00:23', '2023-07-12 11:00:23'),
(60, 'Finalizing the Action Plan and Task Assignments:\nAn action plan was finalized, outlining the tasks necessary to execute the plans. Responsibilities were assigned accordingly.', '10:05:00', 53, '2023-07-12 11:00:55', '2023-07-12 11:00:55'),
(61, 'Closing Remarks\nThe meeting was concluded by Mr. Majid Amin at 10:10, with thanks given to all attendees for their valuable contributions.', '10:10:00', 53, '2023-07-12 11:02:39', '2023-07-12 11:02:39'),
(62, 'Introduction and Welcome:\nMr. Majed Amin welcomed Mr. Mohammed Al-dawy and outlined the purpose of the meeting.', '13:00:00', 54, '2023-07-12 11:13:08', '2023-07-12 11:13:08'),
(63, 'Discussion and Agreement on Purchase of Buffalo Calf and Cow Calf:\nIt was agreed to purchase a buffalo calf weighing 460 kilograms for an amount of 55,200 pounds, and a cow calf weighing 446 kilograms for an amount of 57,980 pounds.', '13:04:00', 54, '2023-07-12 11:13:50', '2023-07-12 11:13:50'),
(64, 'Arrangement for Slaughter with Butcher Ahmed Al-Shafi\'i:\n it was agreed that the calves would be slaughtered by butcher Ahmed Al-Shafi\'i for a fee of 3000 L.E.', '13:10:00', 54, '2023-07-12 11:14:48', '2023-07-12 11:18:42'),
(65, 'Transportation of Packed Meat Arrangement with Taxi Owner Bilal Arz:\n it was agreed to transport the packed meat by taxi to its owner Bilal Arz for the governorates of Cairo, Alexandria, and Beheira in the cities of Damanhour and Hosh Issa for an amount of 2600 L.E.', '13:15:00', 54, '2023-07-12 11:15:43', '2023-07-12 11:18:23'),
(66, 'Arrangement for Purchase of Plastic Bags for Packing:\nit was agreed to buy 4 kilos of plastic bags for packing in the amount of 300 pounds.', '13:20:00', 54, '2023-07-12 11:16:22', '2023-07-12 11:16:22'),
(67, 'Closing Remarks:\nThe meeting was concluded by Mr. Majed Amin at exactly 13:40 in the evening, with thanks given to Mr. Mohammed Al-dawy for his cooperation.', '13:40:00', 54, '2023-07-12 11:18:00', '2023-07-12 11:18:00'),
