(104, '-Closing Remarks\nsummarized the meeting\'s outcomes and discussed the next steps', '10:15:00', 70, '2023-07-17 13:16:50', '2023-07-17 13:16:50'),
(105, 'Welcome and introductions:\nThe meeting was called to order by Mr. Maged Amin at 09:30 AM. All attendees were present.', '09:30:00', 50, '2023-07-23 13:10:02', '2023-07-23 13:10:02'),
(106, 'Discussion of the importance of Ramadan as a time of giving:\nThe group discussed the importance of Ramadan as a time of giving and charity. They talked about how Ramadan is a month of spiritual reflection and renewal, and how it is a time to focus on helping those in need.', '09:35:00', 50, '2023-07-23 13:10:39', '2023-07-23 13:10:39'),
(107, 'Discussion of Ramadan bags as a way to show support and kindness towards needy families: \nThe group discussed how Ramadan bags are a way to show support and kindness towards needy families. They talked about how the bags can provide families with essential food items, and how they can help to lift some of the financial burden during this difficult time.', '09:50:00', 50, '2023-07-23 13:11:35', '2023-07-23 13:11:35'),
(108, 'Discussion of how Heliopolis Group seeks to reach as many eligible and needy families as possible this month: \nThe group discussed how New Egypt Group seeks to reach as many eligible and needy families as possible this month. They talked about their plans to distribute Ramadan bags to families in need, and they discussed how they will be working to reach as many families as possible.', '09:55:00', 50, '2023-07-23 13:13:24', '2023-07-23 13:13:24'),
(109, 'Next steps: The group agreed to finalize their plans for distributing Ramadan bags, and they agreed to meet again to discuss their progress', '10:00:00', 50, '2023-07-23 13:14:10', '2023-07-23 13:14:10'),
(110, 'The meeting was called to order by Mr. Maged Amin at 09:30 AM. All attendees were present.', '09:30:00', 56, '2023-07-23 18:57:26', '2023-07-23 18:57:26'),
(111, 'A brief presentation of what was done at the first meeting of the Ramadan Kareem event for 2023 :\nMr.Maged Amin gave a brief presentation of what was done at the first meeting of the Ramadan Kareem event for 2023. The main topics discussed were the contents of the Ramadan food carton, the places of geographical distribution of the Ramadan cartoon in Egypt, and the practical steps to implement the task.', '09:35:00', 56, '2023-07-23 19:01:11', '2023-07-23 19:01:11'),
(112, 'View and discuss the contents of the Ramadan food carton :\nThe board members viewed and discussed the contents of the Ramadan food carton. They were pleased with the selection of food items and the overall quality of the carton.', '09:45:00', 56, '2023-07-23 19:02:23', '2023-07-23 19:02:23'),
(113, 'Presentation and discussion of the places of geographical distribution of the Ramadan cartoon in Egypt :\nThe board members also discussed the places of geographical distribution of the Ramadan cartoon in Egypt. They decided to focus on distributing the cartons to low-income areas  .', '09:55:00', 56, '2023-07-23 19:03:55', '2023-07-23 19:05:03'),
(114, 'Schedule a third meeting to discuss practical steps to implement the task :\nThe board members scheduled a third meeting to discuss practical steps to implement the task', '10:10:00', 56, '2023-07-23 19:06:44', '2023-07-23 19:06:44'),
(115, '- Welcome and Introduction\nMr.Maged Amin opened the meeting and provided a recap of the previous meeting\'s decisions and action items.', '09:30:00', 71, '2023-07-25 11:34:21', '2023-07-25 11:42:38'),
(116, '- Review of food suppliers :\nThe Board Members reviewed a number of suppliers and Hyper One was chosen.', '09:35:00', 71, '2023-07-25 11:35:35', '2023-07-25 11:42:49'),
(117, '- Discussion of Ramadan carton contents :\nThe second item on the agenda was the discussion of Ramadan carton contents. The prices and types of food commodities included in the carton were discussed.', '09:50:00', 71, '2023-07-25 11:39:12', '2023-07-25 11:39:12'),
(118, '- Review of volunteer registration process:\nThe volunteer registration website was reviewed and the volunteers coordinator answered questions from the Board Members.', '10:00:00', 71, '2023-07-25 11:40:32', '2023-07-25 11:42:58'),
(119, '- Discussion of Ramadan bag delivery process\nThe volunteers coordinator outlined the process for delivering the Ramadan bags to the needy and registering them on the website.', '10:10:00', 71, '2023-07-25 11:42:17', '2023-07-25 11:42:17'),
(120, '-Introduction and Welcome :\nMr.Maged Amin opened the meeting, The meeting was called to order by Mr. Maged Amin', '09:30:00', 72, '2023-07-25 18:15:12', '2023-07-26 15:31:04'),
(121, '- Review of Purpose and Goals of the Charity Iftar :\nThe purpose and goals of the charity Iftar were reviewed. The goal is to raise money to help orphaned children and to support the people in need in Upper Egypt who live in the village of Qubeiba.', '09:35:00', 72, '2023-07-25 18:16:22', '2023-07-25 18:16:22'),
(122, '- Discussion of Fundraising Strategies :\nFundraising strategies discussed. The members of the Board of Directors decided to focus on collecting donations after the Iftar, during the celebration, and after showing the videos that show the conditions of the village.', '09:50:00', 72, '2023-07-25 18:37:05', '2023-07-25 18:37:05'),
(123, '- Review of Logistics and Venue\nThe logistics of the Iftar were reviewed. The board members decided to hold the Iftar in an elegant and appropriate place', '10:00:00', 72, '2023-07-25 18:40:10', '2023-07-25 18:40:10'),
(124, '- Next steps\nNext steps were discussed. The board members decided to create a fundraising campaign and to start planning the fundraising events. They also decided to  reserve a venue.', '10:10:00', 72, '2023-07-25 19:10:19', '2023-07-25 19:10:19'),
(125, '- Welcome and Introduction :\nMr.Maged Amin welcomed all attendees and outlined the purpose of the meeting', '09:30:00', 73, '2023-07-26 10:51:14', '2023-07-26 11:01:29'),
(126, '- Review of Previous Meeting :\nThe minutes of the previous meeting were reviewed', '09:35:00', 73, '2023-07-26 10:53:49', '2023-07-26 11:03:52'),
(127, '- Review of Potential Venues :\nThe potential venues for the Iftar were reviewed. The board members discussed the pros and cons of each venue', '09:45:00', 73, '2023-07-26 11:01:08', '2023-07-26 11:01:08'),
(128, '- Review and Discussion of Ramadan Iftar Program :\nThe Ramadan Iftar program was reviewed and discussed. The board members discussed the menu, the entertainment, and the speakers for the event. They also discussed how to promote the event and how to collect donations.', '09:55:00', 73, '2023-07-26 11:14:38', '2023-07-26 11:14:38'),
(129, '- Next Steps:\nNext steps were discussed. The board members decided to finalize the details of the Iftar program and to start promoting the event.', '10:10:00', 73, '2023-07-26 11:15:45', '2023-07-26 11:15:45'),
(130, '- Welcome and introductions :\nMr, Maged Amin welcomed all attendees and outlined the purpose of the meeting', '09:30:00', 74, '2023-07-26 13:21:32', '2023-07-26 13:21:32'),
(131, '- Review of previous meeting minutes :\n The previous meeting minutes were reviewed', '09:35:00', 74, '2023-07-26 13:22:46', '2023-07-26 13:22:46'),
(132, '- Discussion of event planning :\nThe group agreed to invite several important figures to the Ramadan Iftar ceremony, including : Sheikh Dr. Ahmed Dowidar, who is the head of the Islamic Center in Manhattan, Mrs,  Nadia Henry, a parliament member. \nThe group also agreed to hold the event at Sultan Cuisine in New Jersey, as the members found it to be a suitable and affordable venue.', '09:45:00', 74, '2023-07-26 13:27:23', '2023-07-26 13:27:23'),
(133, '- Fundraising Target :\n The group aspires to raise almost $ 20,000 for the village of Al-Qubeiba', '09:55:00', 74, '2023-07-26 13:31:07', '2023-07-26 13:31:07'),
(134, '- Welcome and introductions :\nThe meeting was called to order at 9:30 AM by Mr, Maged Amin.', '09:30:00', 75, '2023-07-26 20:50:01', '2023-07-26 20:50:01'),
(135, '- The discussion of campaign goals began.\nThe group discussed the need for infrastructure development in the village, such as roads, schools, and hospitals.\nThe group also discussed the need for health services in the village, such as primary care, maternal and child health, and mental health services.', '09:35:00', 75, '2023-07-26 20:50:59', '2023-07-26 20:50:59'),
(136, '- The group then discussed fundraising strategies:\nThe members discussed the implementation of advertising campaigns to raise awareness of the problems of the village and the importance of contributing to its development', '09:50:00', 75, '2023-07-26 20:53:34', '2023-07-26 20:53:34'),
(137, '- The meeting adjourned at 10:10', '10:10:00', 75, '2023-07-26 20:55:50', '2023-07-26 20:56:02'),
(138, '- Welcome and introductions :\nMr.Maged Amin opened the meeting and provided a recap of the previous meeting\'s decisions and action items.', '09:30:00', 76, '2023-07-27 12:29:10', '2023-07-27 12:29:10'),
(139, '- Review of previous meeting minutes :\nThe previous meeting minutes were reviewed', '09:35:00', 76, '2023-07-27 12:34:39', '2023-07-27 12:34:39'),
(140, '- Discussion of campaign goals :\n\n1 - The members discussed the need for infrastructure development in the village, such as roads, hospitals and Disinfection and cleaning of canals .\n\n2 - The members also discussed the need for health services in the village, such as primary care, maternal and child health .\n\n3 - The members also discussed the need for agricultural development in the village. They felt that this was an important way to improve the livelihoods of the villagers, and that it would also help to make the village more sustainable.\n\n4 - The members discussed the need to beautify the village. They felt that this would make the village more attractive to visitors and investors, and that it would also improve the quality of life for the villagers.', '09:55:00', 76, '2023-07-27 12:44:54', '2023-07-27 12:44:54'),
(141, '- Fundraising strategies :\n1 - The members agreed on the need to visit the village, photograph it and make a campaign to raise awareness of the needs of the village to become a sustainable village.\n\n2 - Designing a number of videos showing information about the village and its needs to raise public awareness and invite the public to support the village', '10:10:00', 76, '2023-07-27 12:56:17', '2023-07-27 12:56:17'),
(142, 'Mr.Maged Amin opened the meeting and provided a recap of the previous meeting\'s decisions and action items.', '09:30:00', 77, '2023-07-27 14:59:40', '2023-07-27 14:59:40'),
(143, '- Review of previous meeting minutes :\nThe previous meeting minutes were reviewed and approved', '09:35:00', 77, '2023-07-27 15:02:33', '2023-07-27 15:02:33'),
(144, '- Discussion of meeting with representatives from the village\nThe discussion of meeting with representatives from the village began.\n- The group listened to the representatives from the village, who mentioned that the health unit is in need of medical support as it suffers from a shortage of medical supplies.\n\n-The group also listened to the representatives from the village, who mentioned that the water channels in the village need to be cleaned and disinfected.\n\n- The group also listened to the representatives from the village, who mentioned that the people of the village need to raise their awareness of sustainable development.', '09:40:00', 77, '2023-07-27 15:11:19', '2023-07-27 15:11:19'),
(145, '- Next Steps :\n The members agreed to work with the village council to organize a cleanup and disinfection of the water channels.', '10:15:00', 77, '2023-07-27 15:21:17', '2023-07-27 15:21:17'),
(146, '- Welcome and Introduction :\nThe meeting began with Mr.Maged Amin welcoming the attendees and introducing the purpose of the meeting. The meeting then reviewed the agenda for the meeting.', '09:30:00', 57, '2023-07-28 13:11:49', '2023-07-28 13:12:15'),
(147, '- Review a number of food suppliers to choose the best of them according to the criteria agreed by the board of directors :\nThe meeting then reviewed a number of food suppliers. The attendees discussed the criteria that they would use to choose the best supplier, such as the quality of the food, the price of the food, and the delivery time. The attendees ultimately decided to choose the supplier that had the best overall rating.', '09:35:00', 57, '2023-07-28 13:13:43', '2023-07-28 13:13:43'),
(148, '-Discuss the quantities and types of food items that will be presented in this year\'s Ramadan bags :\nThe meeting then discussed the quantities and types of food items that would be presented in this year\'s Ramadan bag. The attendees discussed the needs of the people that they would be distributing the food to, and they decided on a list of items that would be most helpful.', '09:50:00', 57, '2023-07-28 13:15:37', '2023-07-28 13:15:37'),
(149, '-  Review the initial cost based on the quantities proposed to be distributed geographically  :\nThe meeting then reviewed the initial cost of the food based on the quantities proposed to be distributed geographically. The attendees discussed the budget for the initiative, and they agreed to make some adjustments to the quantities of food items that would be distributed', '10:10:00', 57, '2023-07-28 13:16:41', '2023-07-28 13:16:41'),
(150, '- Set a date for the fourth meeting to review practical steps for implementation on the ground :\nThe meeting concluded with a discussion of the next steps. The attendees agreed to meet again in one week to review the practical steps for implementation on the ground.', '10:25:00', 57, '2023-07-28 13:17:59', '2023-07-28 13:17:59'),
(151, '-Introduction and Welcome :\nThe meeting commenced with a warm welcome from the chairperson. All attendees were introduced, and the purpose of the meeting was outlined.', '09:30:00', 79, '2023-08-03 11:45:41', '2023-08-03 11:45:41'),
(152, '- Review of Ramadan 2020 Campaign for Qubeiba Village :\nThe team presented a comprehensive review of the Ramadan 2020 campaign that took place in Qubeiba village. The campaign\'s objectives, execution, and outcomes were discussed. Feedback from villagers, volunteers, and stakeholders was shared, along with areas of success and potential improvements for future campaigns.', '09:35:00', 79, '2023-08-03 11:46:21', '2023-08-03 11:46:21'),
