(192, '- Welcome and introductions :\nThe meeting was called to order at 09:300 AM by Mr.Maged Amin', '09:30:00', 86, '2023-08-06 19:07:17', '2023-08-06 19:07:17'),
(193, '- Discussion of foodstuffs to be distributed :\n\nThe group discussed the foodstuffs that would be distributed to the needy people of Saft Turab during the month of Ramadan. The following items were agreed upon:\nRice\nBeans\nOil\nFlour\nDates\nSugar\nand more', '09:35:00', 86, '2023-08-06 19:08:17', '2023-08-06 19:08:17'),
(194, '-Discussion of logistics of distribution :\nThe group discussed the logistics of distribution. It was decided that the foodstuffs would be distributed to the needy people of Saft Turab', '10:00:00', 86, '2023-08-06 19:11:39', '2023-08-06 19:13:54'),
(195, '- The following action items were identified:\nContact Representative of the group in the village of Safat TRAB to arrange for distribution of foodstuffs .\n\n- Finalize the list of foodstuffs to be distributed', '10:10:00', 86, '2023-08-06 19:16:49', '2023-08-06 19:16:49'),
(196, '- The meeting was called to order at 09:30 AM', '09:30:00', 87, '2023-08-07 15:43:40', '2023-08-07 15:43:40'),
(197, '- Review of the importance of biogas units :\n\nThe meeting began with a review of the importance of biogas units in the Sustainable Development Plan for the village of Saft Turab. Biogas units can provide a clean and renewable source of energy, as well as a way to dispose of organic waste. They can also help to improve air quality and reduce greenhouse gas emissions.', '09:35:00', 87, '2023-08-07 15:45:34', '2023-08-07 15:45:34'),
(198, 'Transfer of $1000 to build a biogas unit in Saft Turab :\nThe board then discussed the transfer of $1000 to build a biogas unit in Saft Turab. The board unanimously approved the transfer of funds.\n\nThe board discussed the following factors in making their decision:\n\nThe cost of building a biogas unit.\nThe benefits of having a biogas unit in the village.\nThe availability of funding for the project.', '10:00:00', 87, '2023-08-07 15:47:45', '2023-08-07 15:47:45');
INSERT INTO `minutes` (`id`, `subject`, `time`, `meeting_id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(199, 'The meeting was adjourned at 10:15 AM.', '10:15:00', 87, '2023-08-07 15:50:41', '2023-08-07 15:50:41'),
(200, 'Call to Order: Official start of the meeting', '09:30:00', 88, '2023-08-09 19:35:01', '2023-08-09 19:35:01'),
(201, 'Approval of Previous Minutes: The minutes from the previous meeting were approved.', '09:35:00', 88, '2023-08-09 19:35:40', '2023-08-09 19:35:40'),
(202, 'Progress Report: The progress made in purchasing and distributing food to the needy in the village of Safat TRAB during Ramadan was discussed.', '09:40:00', 88, '2023-08-09 19:36:24', '2023-08-09 19:36:24'),
(203, 'Challenges and Solutions: Several challenges were identified, including limited resources and transportation issues. Possible solutions were brainstormed, such as seeking additional donations or partnering with local organizations.', '09:50:00', 88, '2023-08-09 19:37:16', '2023-08-09 19:37:16'),
(204, 'Feedback from Beneficiaries: Positive feedback was received from the beneficiaries of the food distribution program. They expressed gratitude for the support and highlighted the positive impact it had on their lives.', '10:00:00', 88, '2023-08-09 19:38:27', '2023-08-09 19:38:27'),
(205, 'Evaluation of Budget: The budget allocation was evaluated and found to be sufficient to cover the expenses incurred during the program.', '10:10:00', 88, '2023-08-09 19:39:02', '2023-08-09 19:39:02'),
(206, 'Logistics and Coordination: The logistical arrangements and coordination efforts were deemed effective, ensuring smooth distribution to the needy individuals in the village.', '10:15:00', 88, '2023-08-09 19:41:40', '2023-08-09 19:41:40'),
(207, 'Recognition and Appreciation: Gratitude was expressed to all individuals  that contributed to the success of the Campaign. Their support was acknowledged and appreciated.', '10:20:00', 88, '2023-08-09 19:53:56', '2023-08-09 19:53:56'),
(208, '-Introduction and Welcome :\n\nThe meeting started with an introduction of all attendees and a warm welcome to everyone.\n\nThe purpose of the meeting was explained: to discuss a visit to the Children\'s Cancer Hospital 57357 and organizing a special children\'s party for the sick children.', '09:30:00', 89, '2023-08-10 20:42:00', '2023-08-10 20:42:00'),
(209, '- Recap of the Event Plan\n\nA brief overview of the planned visit to the hospital and the children\'s party was provided.\n\nThe goals of the event were reiterated: bringing joy to the hearts of the sick children, distributing gifts, and showing support in their fight against cancer.', '09:35:00', 89, '2023-08-10 20:43:15', '2023-08-10 20:43:15'),
(210, '- Assign Roles and Responsibilities\n\nKey roles for the event were identified, including event coordination, gift procurement, entertainment arrangement, logistics, and communication.\n\nResponsibilities were assigned to each team member based on their expertise and availability.', '09:45:00', 89, '2023-08-10 20:44:17', '2023-08-10 20:44:17'),
(211, '- Logistics and Timeline Discussion\n\nThe logistics of the visit and party were discussed, including the date, time, and duration of the event.\n\nThe number of participants , and necessary permissions were addressed.\n\nIt was decided to ensure compliance with all hospital protocols and safety measures.', '10:00:00', 89, '2023-08-10 20:46:31', '2023-08-10 20:46:31'),
(212, '- Entertainment and Activities\n\nCreative ideas for entertaining and engaging the children were brainstormed.\n\nSuggestions included hiring performers such as magicians, clowns, or musicians, and organizing interactive games and crafts.\n\nThe aim was to create a joyful and memorable experience for the children.', '10:15:00', 89, '2023-08-10 20:47:30', '2023-08-10 20:47:30'),
(213, '- Volunteer Recruitment \n\nThe need for volunteers was discussed, and the required number was determined.', '10:20:00', 89, '2023-08-10 20:48:47', '2023-08-10 20:48:47'),
(214, '- Introduction and Welcome :\n\nIntroduce all attendees and thank them for their participation', '09:30:00', 90, '2023-08-11 18:52:14', '2023-08-11 18:52:14'),
(215, '- Review of minutes from previous meeting: \nThe minutes from the previous meeting were reviewed and approved', '09:35:00', 90, '2023-08-11 18:55:48', '2023-08-11 18:55:48'),
(216, '- Discussion of proposal to transfer funds from Support Saft Turab Campaign to support the health unite in Saft Turab Village: \n\nThe board discussed the proposal in detail. They reviewed the financial situation of the health unite, the needs of the community, and the impact that the funds would have. The board unanimously approved the proposal to transfer the funds.', '09:40:00', 90, '2023-08-11 18:58:31', '2023-08-11 18:58:31'),
(217, 'Next steps:\nThe board will finalize the paperwork to transfer the funds.', '10:00:00', 90, '2023-08-11 19:04:40', '2023-08-11 19:04:40'),
(218, '- Introductions and welcome\nMr. Maged Amin the club founder welcomed all attendees and explained the purpose of the meeting', '09:30:00', 91, '2023-08-13 15:51:57', '2023-08-13 15:51:57'),
(219, '- Review of minutes from previous meeting :\nThe minutes from the previous meeting were reviewed and approved.', '09:35:00', 91, '2023-08-13 15:53:52', '2023-08-13 15:53:52'),
(220, '- Discussion of proposal to transfer funds from Support Saft Turab Campaign to support the health unite in Saft Turab Village: \nThe board discussed the proposal in detail. They reviewed the financial situation of the health unite, the needs of the community, and the impact that the funds would have. The board unanimously approved the proposal to transfer the funds.', '09:45:00', 91, '2023-08-13 15:56:54', '2023-08-13 15:56:54'),
(221, '- Next steps: \nThe board will finalize the paperwork to transfer the funds.', '10:10:00', 91, '2023-08-13 15:58:29', '2023-08-13 15:58:29'),
(222, '- Closing Remarks and Adjournment:\nThe meeting was concluded by Mr.Maged Amin at 10:30, with thanks given to all attendees for their valuable contributions.', '10:30:00', 91, '2023-08-13 17:23:23', '2023-08-13 17:23:23'),
(223, 'The meeting was called to order at 9:30 am by Mr. Maged Amin. The attendees introduced themselves and reviewed the agenda', '09:30:00', 93, '2023-09-10 16:09:40', '2023-09-10 16:09:40'),
(224, 'Introduce the purpose and significance of developing a state-of-the-art website for New Egypt Group', '09:40:00', 93, '2023-09-10 16:27:14', '2023-09-10 16:27:14'),
(225, 'Present the key features and objectives of the website, emphasizing its importance in reaching a global audience', '09:50:00', 93, '2023-09-10 16:29:14', '2023-09-10 16:29:14'),
(226, 'Engage in a discussion regarding the website\'s design elements and content requirements', '10:00:00', 93, '2023-09-10 16:30:15', '2023-09-10 16:30:15'),
(227, '- The meeting was called to order at 9:30 am by Mr. Maged Amin, Group Founder. The attendees introduced themselves and reviewed the agenda', '09:30:00', 94, '2023-09-14 14:44:00', '2023-09-14 14:47:35'),
(228, '- The meeting began with a discussion of the need for food support in Al-qubeiba village. Participants shared their knowledge of the village\'s population and economy, and discussed the challenges that many residents face in accessing food. It was noted that a significant number of residents are unemployed or underemployed, and that many families are struggling to meet their basic needs.', '09:50:00', 94, '2023-09-14 14:47:15', '2023-09-14 14:47:50'),
(229, '- The members discussed the purchase of a set of necessary food items and the packaging of these food items such as rice, sugar, legumes and many other food items', '10:10:00', 94, '2023-09-14 14:54:52', '2023-09-14 14:54:52'),
(230, '- The members discussed the available information about the best food suppliers and the comparison between their products and their different prices and the discussion was based on the best and the finest', '10:15:00', 94, '2023-09-14 15:01:02', '2023-09-14 15:04:48'),
(231, '-The meeting was closed and another date was agreed for the second meeting', '10:20:00', 94, '2023-09-14 15:06:38', '2023-09-14 15:06:51'),
(232, '-  Introduction and Welcome :\n- The meeting was called to order at 9:30 am by Mr. Maged Amin,  The group Founder. The attendees introduced themselves and reviewed the agenda', '09:30:00', 95, '2023-09-15 16:05:36', '2023-09-17 11:32:35'),
(233, '-  Review of Current Food Needs in Al-Qubeiba Village :\n- An overview of the current food situation in Al-Qubeiba Village was provided, and the specific food items required and quantities needed to support the community were discussed.', '09:35:00', 95, '2023-09-15 16:34:16', '2023-09-15 16:41:55'),
(234, '-  Identify Potential Suppliers of Foodstuffs :\n-  A brainstorming session was conducted, and a list of potential suppliers was compiled.The Factors such as cost, quality, and reliability were considered when selecting suppliers.', '09:50:00', 95, '2023-09-15 16:40:26', '2023-09-15 16:42:20'),
(235, '-  Evaluation and Selection of Suppliers :\n- The potential suppliers were evaluated based on the collected information.\n- The pros and cons of each supplier were discussed, and a decision was made.', '10:00:00', 95, '2023-09-15 16:45:18', '2023-09-15 16:58:08'),
(236, '-  Planning the Distribution Process :\n- The logistics of distributing foodstuffs to the needy in Al-Qubeiba Village were discussed.\n- The most effective and efficient methods for reaching the target recipients were explored.', '10:20:00', 95, '2023-09-15 16:57:55', '2023-09-15 16:57:55'),
(237, '-  Conclusion :\n\n- The key discussion points and decisions made during the meeting were summarized.\n- Gratitude was expressed to all participants for their valuable input and commitment to improving food support in the community.', '10:30:00', 95, '2023-09-15 17:16:27', '2023-09-15 17:16:27'),
(238, 'The meeting started with an introduction of all attendees and a warm welcome to everyone', '09:30:00', 96, '2023-09-17 20:17:37', '2023-09-17 20:17:37'),
(239, '-  Receiving and Packing of Foodstuffs\n\nDiscuss the process of receiving the food items from the supplier\n\nBrainstorm ideas on efficient packing and organization methods\n\nAddress food safety and hygiene measures that need to be followed during the packing process', '09:35:00', 96, '2023-09-17 20:22:16', '2023-09-17 20:22:16'),
(240, '- Proposed Amount for Purchase and Receipt of Foodstuffs\n\nReview the estimated number of beneficiaries in Al-Qubeiba village and their immediate needs\n\nDetermine the appropriate quantity of foodstuffs to be purchased\n\nConsider factors such as storage capacity, shelf life, and nutritional requirements when finalizing the proposed amount', '09:50:00', 96, '2023-09-17 20:23:03', '2023-09-17 20:23:03'),
(241, '- Organizational Matters\n\n\nMeet with the representative of the group in Al-Qubeiba village\n\nDiscuss specific requirements and challenges unique to the village\n\nCoordinate efforts between the board, the village representative, and the volunteers\n\nDefine roles and responsibilities for effective collaboration', '10:00:00', 96, '2023-09-17 20:23:35', '2023-09-17 20:23:35'),
(242, '- Action Planning\n\nCreate an action plan outlining specific steps and responsibilities for each aspect discussed (receiving, packing, purchase, receipt, organizational matters)\n\nSet realistic targets and deadlines for each action item', '10:20:00', 96, '2023-09-17 20:24:01', '2023-09-17 20:24:01'),
(243, '- Conclusion\n\nSummarize the key discussion points and decisions made during the meeting\n\nExpress gratitude to all participants for their contributions and commitment to the food distribution initiative', '10:30:00', 96, '2023-09-17 20:24:46', '2023-09-17 20:24:46'),
(244, '- Introduction and Welcome\n\nAttendees introduced themselves.\n\nThe purpose of the meeting was stated as discussing the transfer of funds to support people in need with food in Al-Qubeiba Village.', '09:30:00', 97, '2023-09-18 16:46:03', '2023-09-18 16:46:03'),
(245, '-  Overview of the Situation in Al-Qubeiba Village\n\nInformation about the current situation in Al-Qubeiba Village was shared, including the number of people in need and their specific requirements.\n\nChallenges faced by the community were discussed to gain a better understanding of the situation.', '09:50:00', 97, '2023-09-18 16:47:21', '2023-09-18 16:47:21'),
(246, '- Determining the Required Funds\n\nThe estimated amount of funds needed to adequately support the people in need with food in Al-Qubeiba Village was discussed.\n\nFactors such as the number of beneficiaries, duration of support required, and cost of essential food items were taken into consideration.', '10:00:00', 97, '2023-09-18 16:49:23', '2023-09-18 16:49:23'),
(247, '- Identifying Funding Sources\n\nPotential funding sources, including existing budgets, donations, grants, or partnerships, were explored.\n\nLimitations or restrictions associated with each funding source were discussed to make informed decisions.', '10:15:00', 97, '2023-09-18 17:59:57', '2023-09-18 17:59:57'),
(248, '- Decision-Making Process\n\nCriteria and considerations for allocating the funds were discussed.\n\nA transparent decision-making process was established to ensure fairness and accountability.', '10:20:00', 97, '2023-09-18 18:00:31', '2023-09-18 18:01:53'),
(249, '- Action Planning\n\nAn action plan was created to outline the steps required to transfer the funds.\n\nRoles and responsibilities for financial management, documentation, and communication were defined.', '10:25:00', 97, '2023-09-18 18:01:40', '2023-09-18 18:01:40'),
(250, '- Execution and Monitoring\n\nA timeline was established for executing the fund transfer process.\n\nA monitoring mechanism was put in place to track the progress and impact of the support provided.', '10:35:00', 97, '2023-09-18 18:05:28', '2023-09-18 18:05:28'),
(251, '- Communication and Reporting\n\nThe communication strategy for informing the community and stakeholders about the fund transfer and its purpose was discussed.\n\nReporting requirements to ensure transparency and accountability were outlined.', '10:45:00', 97, '2023-09-18 18:06:06', '2023-09-18 18:06:06'),
(252, '- Conclusion\n\nThe key discussion points and decisions made during the meeting were summarized.\n\nGratitude was expressed to all participants for their contributions and commitment to supporting the community in Al-Qubeiba Village.', '11:00:00', 97, '2023-09-18 18:07:20', '2023-09-18 18:07:20'),
(253, '- Welcome and Introduction\nIntroduce all attendees and establish a welcoming atmosphere.', '09:30:00', 98, '2023-09-19 10:45:09', '2023-09-19 10:45:09'),
(254, '- Purpose and Background\n\nProvide an overview of the situation and the need for restoring the house.\n\nDiscuss the importance of community support and involvement.', '09:35:00', 98, '2023-09-19 10:45:37', '2023-09-19 10:45:37'),
(255, '- Project Overview\n\nPresent a detailed description of the current condition of the house.\n\nShare any information about the family\'s specific requirements and preferences.\n\nHighlight the timeline for the restoration project.', '10:00:00', 98, '2023-09-19 10:56:23', '2023-09-19 10:56:23'),
(256, 'Next Steps:\n\nThe group will meet again in one week to review the progress of the restoration project and to discuss any next steps', '10:15:00', 98, '2023-09-19 12:02:45', '2023-09-19 12:02:45'),
(257, '- Welcome and Introduction\n\nIntroduce all attendees and establish a welcoming atmosphere.', '09:30:00', 99, '2023-09-19 15:16:46', '2023-09-19 15:16:46'),
(258, '- Logistics and Planning\n\nDiscuss the logistics of the restoration, including required permits, materials, and contractors.\n\nAllocate responsibilities for contacting suppliers, obtaining quotes, and managing the project timeline.', '09:35:00', 99, '2023-09-19 15:17:31', '2023-09-19 15:17:31'),
(259, '- Volunteer Recruitment\n\nIdentify potential volunteers and discuss strategies for recruiting them.\n\nAssign roles and responsibilities for volunteer coordination and management.', '10:00:00', 99, '2023-09-19 15:18:07', '2023-09-19 15:18:07'),
(260, '- Communication and Outreach\n\nDevelop a communication plan to inform the community about the project.\n\nAssign someone to manage social media accounts, create content, and update the community on progress.', '10:15:00', 99, '2023-09-19 15:23:05', '2023-09-19 15:23:05'),
(261, '- Budgeting and Financial Management\n\nDiscuss budgetary considerations and identify potential sources of funding.\n\nAppoint a treasurer to oversee financial transactions and record keeping.', '10:20:00', 99, '2023-09-19 15:23:40', '2023-09-19 15:25:34'),
(262, 'Next Steps \n\nSummarize the key decisions and action points from the meeting.\n\nAssign specific tasks to individuals with clear deadlines.\n\nSet a date for the next meeting and establish regular progress updates.', '10:30:00', 99, '2023-09-19 15:25:52', '2023-09-19 15:25:52'),
(263, '- Welcome and Introductions :\n\n-Briefly introduce all attendees\n\n-Emphasize the importance of the meeting', '09:30:00', 100, '2023-09-20 10:34:19', '2023-09-20 11:01:46'),
(264, '- Review of Project Objective :\n\n- Discuss the objective: Supporting the village of Al-Qubeiba with food during the month of Ramadan\n\n- Highlight the significance of providing assistance to those in need during this holy month', '09:45:00', 100, '2023-09-20 10:56:21', '2023-09-20 10:59:07'),
(265, '- Overview and Scope :\n\n-Provide an overview of the activity, including its timeline and expected deliverables\n\n-Clarify the scope of the activity and the specific areas it aims to address', '10:00:00', 100, '2023-09-20 11:01:31', '2023-09-20 11:01:31'),
(266, '- Resource Assessment :\n\n-Review available resources, including financial, human, and logistical support\n\n-Identify potential limitations or challenges that may arise during the project implementation', '10:20:00', 100, '2023-09-20 11:03:34', '2023-09-20 11:03:34'),
(267, '- Meeting Conclusion :\n\nThank all participants for their time and contributions\n\nSet the date and time for the next follow-up meeting.', '10:30:00', 100, '2023-09-20 11:04:55', '2023-09-20 11:04:55'),
(268, '- Welcome and Introduction :\n\n-Start the meeting by welcoming all attendees.\n\n-Introduce the purpose of the meeting, which is to discuss sending a sum of $600 for house renovations in the village of Al-qubeiba.', '09:35:00', 101, '2023-09-21 11:38:12', '2023-09-21 11:38:12'),
(269, '- Review of Proposal\n\nPresent the proposal for renovating a house for the needy in Al-qubeiba.\n\nDiscuss the importance and impact of this project on the community.\n\nReview any relevant details, such as the condition of the house, estimated costs, and potential challenges.', '09:45:00', 101, '2023-09-21 11:38:44', '2023-09-21 11:38:44'),
(270, '- Budget Discussion :\n\nEvaluate the proposed budget for the renovation project.', '10:00:00', 101, '2023-09-21 21:13:17', '2023-09-21 21:13:17'),
(271, '-Logistics and Planning\n\n-Determine the timeline for the project, including start and end dates.\n\n-Assign tasks to team members, such as researching contractors, obtaining quotes, and overseeing the renovation process.\n\n-Discuss any necessary permits, legal requirements, or local regulations that need to be considered.', '10:30:00', 101, '2023-09-21 21:15:22', '2023-09-21 21:15:22'),
(272, '-Next Steps :\n-Summarize the key decisions made during the meeting.\n\n-Assign specific action items to individuals, along with deadlines.', '10:40:00', 101, '2023-09-21 21:16:43', '2023-09-21 21:16:43'),
(273, '- Welcome and Introduction :\n   Briefly introduce the purpose of the meeting and the cooperation protocol between the hospital and the \"New Egypt\" Group.', '09:30:00', 102, '2023-10-01 20:48:56', '2023-10-01 20:48:56'),
(274, '- Review of the Annual Camp in Aswan\n   Discuss the details and objectives of the annual camp organized by the Children\'s Cancer Hospital 57357.\n   Highlight the plan to distribute food items to the people of the West Suhail area as part of the camp activities.', '09:40:00', 102, '2023-10-01 20:49:20', '2023-10-01 20:49:20'),
(275, '- New Egypt Group\'s Support :\n   Present the proposal for the New Egypt Group to purchase quantities of foodstuffs to support the charity convoy.\n   Discuss the logistics, budget, and timeline for the procurement and delivery of the food items.', '10:00:00', 102, '2023-10-01 20:49:58', '2023-10-01 20:49:58'),
(276, '- Collaboration and Coordination\n   Explore ways to collaborate effectively between the hospital and the New Egypt Group to ensure the success of the camp and the charity convoy.\n   Assign responsibilities and roles to relevant team members from both organizations.', '10:20:00', 102, '2023-10-01 20:50:18', '2023-10-01 20:50:18'),
(277, 'Next Meeting\n   Decide on the date, time, and agenda for the next meeting', '10:55:00', 102, '2023-10-01 20:51:05', '2023-10-01 20:51:05'),
(278, '- Welcome and Introduction :\n\nCall the meeting to order\n\nIntroduce all attendees\n\nRecap the purpose of the meeting', '09:30:00', 103, '2023-10-02 11:12:20', '2023-10-02 11:12:20'),
(279, '- Annual Camp Support\n\nDiscuss the upcoming annual camp organized by the Children\'s Cancer Hospital in Aswan\n\nPresent details about the camp, including its purpose and activities\n\nEmphasize the importance of supporting the camp through the distribution of foodstuffs', '09:40:00', 103, '2023-10-02 11:13:13', '2023-10-02 11:13:13'),
(280, '- Budget Proposal\n\nPresent the proposed budget for the purchase of foodstuffs\n\nInclude quantities and types of foodstuffs required (rice, pasta, sugar, beans, lentils, sweets)\n\nDiscuss the financial implications and seek input from board members', '10:00:00', 103, '2023-10-02 11:14:18', '2023-10-02 11:14:18'),
(281, '- Coordination with Representative in Egypt\n\nCoordinate with the representative of the group in Egypt\n\nDiscuss their role in facilitating the purchase and transportation of foodstuffs\n\nAddress any concerns or challenges regarding coordination', '10:20:00', 103, '2023-10-02 11:17:52', '2023-10-02 11:17:52'),
(282, '- Supplier Selection :\n\nReview potential suppliers of foodstuffs\n\nConsider factors such as quality, pricing, and reliability\n\nDiscuss the selection process and make necessary decisions', '10:30:00', 103, '2023-10-02 11:18:46', '2023-10-02 11:18:46'),
(283, '- Next Steps and Actions :\n\nResponsibilities were assigned to board members for specific tasks and actions\n\nDeadlines for completing tasks were set', '10:40:00', 103, '2023-10-02 17:19:24', '2023-10-02 17:19:24'),
(284, '- Meeting Conclusion :\n\nThe key points discussed during the meeting were summarized \n\nThe next meeting date and time were confirmed, if necessary\n\nAll attendees were thanked for their participation and contributions', '11:00:00', 103, '2023-10-02 19:22:37', '2023-10-02 19:22:37'),
(285, '- Welcome and Introduction :\n\nBriefly introduce the purpose of the meeting and the topic of discussion.', '09:30:00', 104, '2023-10-04 14:55:55', '2023-10-04 14:55:55'),
(286, '- Proposed Budget for the Charity Convoy :\n\nPresent the proposed budget for the charity convoy.\n\nDiscuss the allocation of funds for purchasing food items.', '10:00:00', 104, '2023-10-04 16:24:11', '2023-10-04 16:24:11'),
(287, '- Agreement on Donation Amounts\n\nDetermine the donation amounts from the New Egypt group towards the charity convoy.\n\nEnsure all participants are in agreement with the suggested donation amounts.', '10:20:00', 104, '2023-10-04 16:25:08', '2023-10-09 10:55:24'),
(288, '- Sending Donations to the Representative\n\nConfirm the process of sending the agreed donation amounts to the representative of the New Egypt group in Egypt.\n\nDiscuss any necessary documentation or procedures required for the transaction.', '10:50:00', 104, '2023-10-04 16:26:15', '2023-10-04 16:26:15'),
(289, '-Summary and Closure :\n\nRecap the main points discussed during the meeting.\n\nThank participants for their contributions and commitment.\n\nSet the date, time, and location for the next meeting if applicable.', '11:10:00', 104, '2023-10-04 16:29:37', '2023-10-04 16:29:37'),
(291, '- Approval of the previous financial meeting minutes\nThe meeting began with the approval of the previous financial meeting minutes. All the attendees agreed to the minutes without any modifications.', '09:30:00', 106, '2023-10-24 19:58:29', '2023-10-24 19:58:29'),
(292, '- Review of the financial report for the last quarter\nMr. Amin presented the financial report for the last quarter. He explained that the organization had received a total of $ 14,609.70 in donations, and had spent $ 500.00 on various activities. He also reported that the organization\'s current balance was $ 14,097.70.', '09:50:00', 106, '2023-10-24 19:59:02', '2023-10-24 19:59:02'),
(293, '- Discussion on the budget for the upcoming event\nThe discussion on the budget for the upcoming event centered on the need to raise funds to ensure its success.', '10:15:00', 106, '2023-10-24 20:00:11', '2023-10-24 20:00:11'),
(294, '- Any other business\nUnder this agenda item, Ms. Naiera brought up the issue of the organization\'s financial policies. She suggested that the organization should establish clear financial policies to guide its operations and ensure transparency. The members agreed to discuss this issue further at the next meeting.', '10:50:00', 106, '2023-10-24 20:04:43', '2023-10-24 20:04:43'),
(295, '- Conclusion:\nThe meeting concluded with the agreement to hold a charity auction as a means to raise funds for the upcoming event. The members also agreed to discuss and establish clear financial policies to guide the organization\'s financial operations. The next financial meeting was scheduled for May 31', '10:55:00', 106, '2023-10-24 20:09:28', '2023-10-24 20:09:28'),
(296, '- Welcome and Introductions\n\nStart the meeting by welcoming all board members and introducing any new attendees.', '09:30:00', 107, '2023-10-29 18:07:16', '2023-10-29 18:07:16'),
(297, '- Approval of Previous Minutes\n\nReview and seek approval for the minutes from the previous board meeting.', '09:40:00', 107, '2023-10-29 18:07:50', '2023-10-29 18:07:50'),
(298, '- Financial Update\n\n-Present the bank statement for review and discussion. \n-Provide a summary of the organization\'s current financial position. \n       - Beginning Balance: $14,097.70\n       - Deposits and Additions: $4,969.70\n       - Ending Balance: $19,065.40\n        - Discuss any significant transactions or \n           changes since the last meeting.\n         - Address any discrepancies or concerns \n           identified in the bank statement.', '09:55:00', 107, '2023-10-29 18:09:43', '2023-10-29 18:10:53'),
(299, '- Budget Review\n\n- Conduct a review of the current budget :\n       -Share updates on revenue and expenses.\n       -  Discuss any variations from the projected budget and \n          reasons behind them.\n- Seek input and suggestions for potential adjustments to ensure \n   financial stability and support ongoing programs.', '10:10:00', 107, '2023-10-29 18:12:45', '2023-10-29 18:12:45'),
(300, '- Fundraising Initiatives\n\n-	Discuss ongoing and upcoming fundraising initiatives. \n	Share progress updates on existing campaigns.\n	Brainstorm new ideas and strategies to enhance fundraising efforts.\n	Allocate responsibilities and set timelines for implementation.', '10:20:00', 107, '2023-10-29 19:24:19', '2023-10-29 19:34:40'),
(301, '- Financial Policies and Procedures\n\n- Review and discuss the organization\'s financial policies and procedures. \n     -Ensure compliance with legal and regulatory \n       requirements.\n     -Identify any gaps or areas for improvement.\n      -Consider if any updates or revisions are necessary.', '11:40:00', 107, '2023-10-29 19:31:34', '2023-10-29 19:34:53'),
(302, '- Audit Preparation\n\n    - Discuss preparations for the upcoming audit. \n    - Review key documents required for the audit process.\n     -Assign responsibilities for gathering and organizing \n  necessary financial information.\n-  Set deadlines and milestones to ensure timely completion of audit-related tasks.', '11:50:00', 107, '2023-10-29 19:34:19', '2023-10-29 19:35:08'),
(303, '- Next Meeting and Adjournment\n\n-Confirm the date, time, and location of the next board meeting.\n-Thank all attendees for their participation.\n-Adjourn the meeting.', '12:00:00', 107, '2023-10-29 19:36:57', '2023-10-29 19:36:57'),
(305, '- Welcome and Introductions\n\n Start the meeting by welcoming all board members and introducing any new attendees.', '09:30:00', 108, '2023-10-29 20:39:43', '2023-10-29 20:39:43'),
(306, '- Review of Bank Statement of June 29, 2018\n\nThe Treasurer presented the bank statement for June 29, 2018. The beginning balance was $19,065.40, deposits and additions were $5,581.70, and the ending balance was $24,647.10.', '09:35:00', 108, '2023-10-29 20:54:44', '2023-10-29 20:54:44'),
(307, '-Discussion of Financial Performance for June 2018\n\nThe Treasurer reviewed the organization\'s financial performance for June 2018. Revenue was higher than expected, due to an increase in grants and donations. Expenses were in line with budget. The organization is in a strong financial position, with a healthy cash reserve.', '09:50:00', 108, '2023-10-29 20:59:25', '2023-10-29 20:59:25'),
(308, 'Approval of Financial Reports for June 2018\n\nThe board unanimously approved the financial reports for June 2018.', '10:25:00', 108, '2023-10-29 21:00:18', '2023-10-29 21:00:18'),
(309, '- Welcome and Introductions\n\n- Start the meeting by welcoming all board members and introducing any new attendees.', '09:30:00', 109, '2023-10-30 14:28:05', '2023-10-30 14:28:05'),
(310, '- Review of Bank Statement of July 31, 2018\n\nThe Treasurer presented the bank statement for July 31, 2018. The beginning balance and ending balance were both $24,647.10, indicating that there was no net activity in the account during the month.', '09:35:00', 109, '2023-10-30 14:28:43', '2023-10-30 14:30:31'),
(311, '- Discussion of Financial Performance for July 2018\n\nThe Treasurer noted that there was no net activity in the account during July 2018, so the organization\'s financial performance for the month was essentially flat.', '09:50:00', 109, '2023-10-30 14:29:37', '2023-10-30 14:30:40'),
(312, '- Approval of Financial Reports for July 2018\n\nThe board unanimously approved the financial reports for July 2018.', '10:10:00', 109, '2023-10-30 14:30:17', '2023-10-30 14:30:17'),
