INSERT INTO `minutes` (`id`, `subject`, `time`, `meeting_id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(400, 'Discussion on the Proposal to Send Funds for Calves:\nAttendees engaged in a thorough discussion regarding the feasibility and potential impact of the proposal.\nConsideration was given to budget constraints, logistics, and the intended beneficiaries.\nPoints of agreement and areas requiring further clarification were noted.', '09:40:00', 105, '2024-03-26 01:07:32', '2024-03-26 01:07:32'),
(401, 'Distribution Plan for Meat to the Needy in Al-qubaiba Village during Eid al-Adha:\n\nMr, Amin outlined the distribution plan for meat to the needy in Al-qubaiba Village during Eid al-Adha.\nThe plan included logistics, coordination with local authorities or organizations, and ensuring equitable distribution.\nAttendees provided feedback on the proposed plan, suggesting adjustments to enhance effectiveness and reach.', '10:15:00', 105, '2024-03-26 01:08:20', '2024-03-26 01:08:20'),
(402, 'The meeting was closed', '11:00:00', 105, '2024-03-26 01:09:35', '2024-03-26 01:09:35'),
(403, '- Opening Remarks :\nThe meeting was called to order by Mr. Amin at 9:30 am', '09:30:00', 127, '2024-04-02 13:43:57', '2024-04-02 13:43:57'),
(404, '-Purpose of the Meeting :\nThe main agenda item was the discussion on launching the Eid al-Fitr Campaign 2024 and inviting donors to purchase Eid clothes for orphaned children', '09:40:00', 127, '2024-04-02 13:44:49', '2024-04-02 13:44:49'),
(405, 'Discussion on Eid al-Fitr Campaign 2024 :\n- Various strategies were discussed to attract donors, including social media campaigns, email newsletters, and collaboration with local businesses for fundraising events.', '10:00:00', 127, '2024-04-02 13:45:53', '2024-04-02 13:45:53'),
(406, 'Allocation of Responsibilities\n- Responsibilities were allocated among the board members, with tasks including contacting potential donors, coordinating logistics for clothing distribution, and managing communication channels.', '10:20:00', 127, '2024-04-02 13:46:47', '2024-04-02 13:46:47'),
(407, '- Setting Deadlines :\nDeadlines were set for each task, with regular follow-ups planned to ensure progress.', '10:30:00', 127, '2024-04-02 13:48:04', '2024-04-02 13:48:04'),
(408, 'Next Steps:\n-Next steps were outlined, including the creation of a detailed campaign plan and the scheduling of follow-up meetings to track progress.', '10:50:00', 127, '2024-04-02 13:56:53', '2024-04-02 13:56:53'),
(409, '- Closing Remarks\nThe meeting was adjourned', '11:00:00', 127, '2024-04-02 13:57:36', '2024-04-02 13:57:36'),
(410, '- Review of Progress Since Last Meeting :\nThe meeting commenced with a review of progress made since the previous meeting, with each member providing updates on their respective tasks and contributions.', '09:30:00', 128, '2024-04-05 19:09:39', '2024-04-05 19:09:39'),
(411, '- Update on Donor Engagement Efforts :\nA comprehensive update was provided on donor engagement efforts, highlighting successful outreach initiatives and areas for improvement.', '09:40:00', 128, '2024-04-05 19:10:19', '2024-04-05 19:10:19'),
(412, '- Discussion on Fundraising Events and Strategies :\nThe board engaged in a lively discussion regarding fundraising events and strategies, exploring innovative ways to maximize donations and support for the campaign.', '09:50:00', 128, '2024-04-05 19:11:02', '2024-04-05 19:11:02'),
(413, '- Evaluation of Logistics for Clothing Distribution :\nLogistics for clothing distribution were evaluated, with a focus on streamlining processes and ensuring efficient delivery to orphaned children.', '10:00:00', 128, '2024-04-05 19:11:37', '2024-04-05 19:11:37'),
(414, '- Addressing Any Challenges or Concerns :\nAny challenges or concerns encountered were addressed collaboratively, with solutions proposed and actions agreed upon to overcome obstacles.', '10:15:00', 128, '2024-04-05 19:12:21', '2024-04-05 19:12:21'),
(415, '- Setting Targets and Deadlines for Next Phase :\nTargets and deadlines for the next phase of the campaign were set, with a clear plan of action outlined to guide future activities.', '10:20:00', 128, '2024-04-05 19:12:56', '2024-04-05 19:12:56'),
(416, '- Next Steps\nNext steps were reiterated, emphasizing the importance of continued teamwork and dedication to achieving the campaign\'s objectives.', '10:30:00', 128, '2024-04-05 19:13:46', '2024-04-05 19:13:46'),
(417, '- Closing Remarks\nThe meeting concluded with closing remarks, expressing gratitude for everyone\'s hard work and commitment to making a positive impact on the lives of orphaned children.', '11:00:00', 128, '2024-04-05 19:14:36', '2024-04-05 19:14:36'),
(418, '- Welcome and Introductions\n\nBrief introduction of attendees.\nPurpose of the meeting: Planning the special Eid celebration for children suffering from cancer at the Art and Healing Center.', '09:30:00', 129, '2024-04-15 12:38:04', '2024-04-15 12:38:04'),
(419, '- Overview of the Event :\n\nReview the objectives of the celebration.\nDiscuss the significance of Eid al-Fitr and its importance for the children.', '09:40:00', 129, '2024-04-15 12:39:30', '2024-04-15 12:39:30'),
(420, '- Discussion on Activities and Program :\n\nBrainstorm ideas for activities and programs to make the day memorable for the children.\nAllocate responsibilities for each activity (e.g., games, arts and crafts, entertainment).', '10:00:00', 129, '2024-04-15 12:41:14', '2024-04-15 12:41:14'),
(421, '- Logistics and Resources\n\nReview available resources (e.g., budget, volunteers, donations).\nDiscuss logistics such as transportation, venue setup, and coordination with the hospital staff.', '10:20:00', 129, '2024-04-15 12:42:00', '2024-04-15 12:42:00'),
(422, '- Eid Clothes and Toy Distribution :\n\nCoordinate the procurement and distribution of Eid clothes and toys for the children.\nEnsure sufficient quantities and variety to cater to different ages and preferences.', '10:55:00', 129, '2024-04-15 12:43:10', '2024-04-15 12:43:10'),
(423, '- Communication and Promotion :\n\nPlan communication strategies to promote the event within the hospital and to potential donors or sponsors.\nAssign tasks for creating promotional materials (e.g., flyers, social media posts).', '11:00:00', 129, '2024-04-15 12:43:59', '2024-04-15 12:43:59'),
(424, '- Volunteer Coordination :\n\nDiscuss recruitment and training of volunteers for the event.\nAssign roles and responsibilities for volunteers during the celebration.', '11:10:00', 129, '2024-04-15 12:48:25', '2024-04-15 12:48:25'),
(425, '- Next Steps and Action Items:\n\nSummarize key decisions and action points.\nAssign tasks with deadlines and responsible persons.', '11:25:00', 129, '2024-04-15 12:49:30', '2024-04-15 12:49:30'),
(426, '- Closing :\n\nRecap the meeting outcomes.\nThank all participants for their contributions.', '11:45:00', 129, '2024-04-15 12:50:55', '2024-04-15 12:50:55'),
(427, '1. Opening\n\nThe meeting was opened by the chairperson, Mr.Nasser Rashad, who welcomed the board members, and all attendees. The purpose of the meeting was to Discuss plans for the upcoming Orphan Day celebration in Gharbia Governorate.', '07:00:00', 130, '2024-04-25 11:17:44', '2024-04-25 11:17:44'),
(428, '2. Overview of the Event\n\nThe chairperson provided an overview of the event, highlighting its significance as the first of its kind organized by New Egypt Foundation in Gharbia Governorate. The event aims to support orphaned children by offering various activities designed to bring joy and happiness.', '07:10:00', 130, '2024-04-25 11:19:05', '2024-04-25 11:19:05'),
(429, '3. Activities Planned\n\n- Sports activities and games for children.\n- Fun competitions and carnivals.\n- Distribution of New clothes, shoes, and gifts.\n- A communal Iftar table for everyone to share.', '08:00:00', 130, '2024-04-25 11:20:08', '2024-04-25 11:20:32'),
(430, '4-  Budget and Sponsorships\n\nA provisional budget was presented by Mohamed El Dewy. Discussions ensued regarding potential sponsorships and donations to cover expenses.', '08:25:00', 130, '2024-04-25 11:23:32', '2024-04-25 11:23:32'),
(431, '5- Closing :\nThe meeting was adjourned by the chairperson, who thanked everyone for their contributions and expressed optimism for the success of the event.', '09:00:00', 130, '2024-04-25 11:25:22', '2024-04-25 11:25:22'),
(432, '- the meeting began by welcoming the members of the board of trustees and the chairman of the board of trustees congratulated the attendees on the issuance of the publicity decision and also gave special thanks to the Department of social affairs for their constructive cooperation .', '07:00:00', 131, '2024-04-26 13:06:49', '2024-05-16 10:53:13'),
(433, '- Welcome, gentlemen, the members of the board of trustees', '07:00:00', 132, '2024-05-13 16:42:35', '2024-05-13 16:42:35'),
(434, '- The previous minutes were read and ratified by the members of the board of trustees', '07:05:00', 132, '2024-05-13 16:43:21', '2024-05-13 16:43:21'),
(435, '- The foundation\'s records were received after approval from the Department of Social Affairs, which was thanked for its support and cooperation', '07:25:00', 132, '2024-05-13 16:44:56', '2024-05-13 16:44:56'),
(436, '- After the discussion, the members of the board of trustees agreed to hand over the financial books and stores to Mr. Mohammed Hamza Abdul Khaleq Al-dawy  and be responsible for it from his date', '08:00:00', 132, '2024-05-13 16:45:58', '2024-05-13 17:58:00'),
(437, '- After the discussion, the members of the board of trustees agreed to hand over the minutes of the board of trustees, founders and administration to Mr. John ( secretary general ) and be responsible for them from the date of the meeting .', '08:15:00', 132, '2024-05-13 18:23:00', '2024-05-13 18:23:00'),
(438, 'The reception of the holy month of Ramadan and the preparation of Ramadan bags were discussed and it was agreed to select three members of the board of trustees and founders to give suggestions and present them to the board of trustees', '08:20:00', 132, '2024-05-13 18:25:30', '2024-05-13 18:25:30'),
(439, '- The meeting was closed at exactly nine o\'clock in the evening', '09:00:00', 132, '2024-05-13 18:27:15', '2024-05-13 18:27:15'),
(440, '- Welcome, gentlemen, the members of the board of trustees', '07:00:00', 133, '2024-05-15 14:40:54', '2024-05-15 14:40:54'),
(441, '- Reading the previous record and ratifying it.', '07:05:00', 133, '2024-05-15 14:42:37', '2024-05-15 14:42:37'),
(442, '- The provision of AIDS during the holy month of Ramadan was discussed for a year 2023 Mr. Majed Mohammed Rashad, one of the founding members of the foundation, started by making an in-kind donation, which is a number of food funds, and also Mr. Nasser Mohammed Rashad ( chairman of the board of trustees ) made a donation in kind, which is a number of food funds were thanked by the members of the board of trustees', '07:20:00', 133, '2024-05-15 14:53:06', '2024-05-16 10:47:59'),
(443, '- It was agreed that the Select Committee at the previous session will complete the distribution of these boxes to the first families after receiving them from Mr. Mohammed Hamza Abdul Khaliq Al-dawy ( treasurer ).', '08:30:00', 133, '2024-05-15 14:54:52', '2024-05-15 14:54:52'),
(444, '- the meeting was closed after discussing all the items and there was no update from the work', '09:00:00', 133, '2024-05-15 14:56:22', '2024-05-15 14:56:22'),
(445, '- The board of Trustees unanimously decided to authorize Professor John Fikri to terminate all registration procedures', '07:10:00', 131, '2024-05-16 10:53:56', '2024-05-16 10:53:56'),
(446, '- The board has authorized Mr. Nasser Mohammed Rashad Amin, chairman of the board of trustees, to conduct all operations of activating the institution\'s bank account', '07:15:00', 131, '2024-05-16 10:54:39', '2024-05-16 10:54:39'),
(447, '- The board unanimously approved the approval of the signature of the chairman of the board of Trustees, the cashier, as well as the secretary general on the foundation\'s account', '07:40:00', 131, '2024-05-16 10:55:24', '2024-05-16 10:55:24'),
(448, '- the members of the board of Trustees approved the institution\'s records and were sealed', '08:20:00', 131, '2024-05-16 10:56:29', '2024-05-16 10:56:29'),
(449, '- A number of publications have been printed, which have been designed, namely subscription books, in-kind donation books, money books and money receipt books', '08:45:00', 131, '2024-05-16 10:57:28', '2024-05-16 10:57:28'),
(450, '- The meeting ended after discussing all the items and there was no update on the work, at exactly nine o\'clock in the evening', '09:00:00', 131, '2024-05-16 10:58:56', '2024-05-16 11:00:21'),
